# LRP Blueprint-First

Lending Readiness Partners is in a **spec-before-code** program.

1. Read `docs/lrp-enterprise/build-bible/README.md` before building product features.
2. Do **not** invent major new UI/API behavior unless the relevant Build Bible volume is `ready-for-build` or the user explicitly asks to draft Bible content.
3. Prefer editing Bible volumes (Stages 1–4) over coding `apps/lrp-web` features until Stage 5 is opened.
4. Existing LRP code is **prototype/reference** unless a volume says keep/refactor/replace.
5. Stack default = shared Verdin platform (`apps/api` + `apps/lrp-web`). Do not migrate to Supabase unless an approved ADR in Vol 24 says so.
6. Product identity: AI-powered Borrower Readiness Platform; advisory scores only; no unsupervised bureau filing.
